h3. Problem Definition

From [Configuring estimation and tracking|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirasoftwareserver073/configuring-estimation-and-tracking-861254451.html], it's stated that:

{quote}
Note that the Estimate field is editable when an issue is in the Backlog, but is not editable once the issue moves into Active sprints.
{quote}

However, in JIRA 7.3 & 7.4, estimate of the issues in Active Sprint is editable & there's a warning is edit side panel shows:

{quote}
Sprint scope will be affected by this action
{quote}


h3. Suggested Solution

Update the JIRA Software documentation to reflect the change in this feature.

h3. Expected Behavior

Reporting is consistent regardless of issue history.
h3. Actual Behavior

If I complete a sprint and send incomplete issues to the backlog or to a different sprint, and then remove one or more of those issues from that sprint, it will be gone from reports.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create at least 1 issue - a.k.a TEST-1;
 # Add TEST-1 to a new sprint - a.k.a Sprint 1;
 # Start Sprint 1;
 # Close Sprint 1 without resolving TEST-1;
 # Add TEST-1 to a new sprint - a.k.a Sprint 2;
 # Start Sprint 2;
 (i) Note the reports - e.g. Sprint Report and Burndown Chart - showing that Sprint 2 started with TEST-1.
 # Remove TEST-1 from Sprint 2;
 (i) Reports for Sprint 2 will not show any reference to TEST-1.

 
h3. Notes

Appears to be a regression from 6.4
h3. Workaround

There is no known workaround at this time.

h3. Summary

When using Microsoft SQL Server, users might be unable to rank issues in JIRA after upgrading from JIRA 6.4 to 7.2+.

h3. Environment
* JIRA 6.4 upgraded to 7.2+
* Microsoft SQL Server 2012 or 2014.
* 1M+ issues.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Upgrade a JIRA instance having 1M+ issues from 6.4 to 7.2.
# Start a re-balance operation to generate load on the database, navigating to *Cog Icon > System > LexoRank Management > Balance all fields*.
# Navigate to a board and change the order of any two issues to rank them.

h3. Expected Results
* JIRA ranks the issues properly.

h3. Actual Results
* JIRA fails to rank the issues, showing the following error message on the UI:
{noformat}
JIRA Software cannot execute the rank operation at this time. Other users may be ranking the issues that you are trying to rank. Please try again later.
{noformat}

After enabling *DEBUG* logging level for the packages {{com.atlassian.greenhopper.service.lexorank}} and {{com.atlassian.greenhopper.manager.lexorank}} the following messages show up in the logs in the file {{atlassian-greenhopper.log}}:
