{noformat}

h3. Notes
* The ranking operation fails because all SQL queries needed for the ranking operation must complete in less than 1500ms. This timeout value is hardcoded and cannot be changed:
{code:java}
public class LexoRankDaoImpl implements LexoRankDao
{
    //(...)
    private static final int LOCK_TIMEOUT_MILLIS = 1500;
{code}
* On JIRA Agile 6.x the {{AO_60DB71_LEXORANK.RANK}} column has the data type {{VARCHAR(255)}}.
* On new JIRA 7.2+ installations the data type on this column was changed to {{NVARCHAR(255)}}.
* The issue happens because JIRA Software does not change the data type of the column {{AO_60DB71_LEXORANK.RANK}} from {{VARCHAR(255)}} to {{NVARCHAR(255)}} during the upgrade to 7.2+, forcing SQL Server to use an inefficient execution plan which is likely to take more than 1500ms to complete, which in turn will trigger the hardcoded timeout in JIRA and the ranking operation will fail.

h3. Workaround
# Stop JIRA.
# Backup your database.
# Delete all indexes from the table {{AO_60DB71_LEXORANK}}, *except for the primary key*.
# Change the data type on the columns {{AO_60DB71_LEXORANK.RANK}} and {{AO_60DB71_LEXORANK.LOCK_HASH}} using these SQL queries:
{code:sql}
ALTER TABLE dbo.AO_60DB71_LEXORANK ALTER COLUMN RANK NVARCHAR(255) NOT NULL;
ALTER TABLE dbo.AO_60DB71_LEXORANK ALTER COLUMN LOCK_HASH NVARCHAR(255) NULL;
{code}
# Run the following SQL queries to flush caches and update statistics on the database:
{code:sql}
DBCC FREEPROCCACHE;
{code}; or for one database:
{code:sql|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#6A8EB3|bgColor=#F8F8F8}
DBCC FLUSHPROCINDB (<dbid>)
{code}
---
{code:sql|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#6A8EB3|bgColor=#F8F8F8}
SP_UPDATESTATS;
{code}; or in the Jira DB:
{code:sql|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#6A8EB3|bgColor=#F8F8F8}
UPDATE STATISTICS;
{code}
# Start JIRA. The indexes for the table {{AO_60DB71_LEXORANK}} will be automatically recreated.

I'm trying to change the date format used with the javascript Date Picker in JIRA.  I want to change to the following format M/d/yy which works with the java format but not the javascript format.  I believe the code for this *should be* %n/%e/%y but all I can get to works is %m/%e/%y . This gives me a 2 digit month instead of single digit month.  Any suggestions?

 
{quote}Example: January 3, 2005 should show as 1/3/05
{quote}

h3. Problem Definition
# JIRA & Bitbucket are behind a Nginx reverse proxy. 
# When changing the allowed ciphers for the SSL session to have a more secured Nginx configuration such as 
{code:borderStyle=solid}
ssl_ciphers ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA384:ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384:ECDHE-RSA-AES265-SHA;
{code}
#* an error will throw mentioning that the certificate is not valid. 

h3. Suggested Solution
Support for strong ciphers such as
{code}
ECDHE-RSA-AES256-SHA384:ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384:ECDHE-RSA-AES265-SHA
{code}

I frequently find myself typing comments in projects that reference another project, e.g. : 
{noformat}
See work completed in DEV-XXX.{noformat}

It would be great if this would automatically create a link in the 'Issue Link' section, so one could easily toggle back and forth between the ticket you are updating and the newly referenced project. Right now, you can click through to the referenced project, but, there is no link to go back to the first ticket (aside from the browser's back button).
